The paper discusses the role of CaMKII in synaptic plasticity and its impact on reward-based neural network optimization. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
